data.objective: Create comprehensive documentation suite for medianest project using MKdocs with Material theme: FIRST analyze the codebase to understand project purpose, features, and architecture. THEN create: 1) MKdocs project structure with Material theme configuration including navigation, search, syntax highlighting, and dark mode; 2) Comprehensive README.md with clear project description, quick start guide, and feature overview; 3) Detailed installation documentation with prerequisites, step-by-step instructions, and common issues; 4) Usage documentation with practical examples and tutorials; 5) API reference documentation for all endpoints/interfaces; 6) Configuration guide covering all options with examples; 7) Architecture documentation explaining system design and components; 8) CONTRIBUTING.md with development setup, coding standards, and PR process; 9) CHANGELOG.md tracking all versions and changes; 10) Troubleshooting guide based on common issues; 11) Security considerations relevant to the project; 12) Deployment guide with best practices; 13) FAQ section. Ensure all documentation is searchable, well-organized, and includes code examples. Configure GitHub Pages deployment for the MKdocs site.
